'''Cannabis in Taiwan''' is illegal. Cannabis is listed as a category 2 narcotic by Narcotics Hazard Prevention Act in the ROC. Possession of a category 2 drug can result in up to three years of imprisonment; planting or trafficking can result in at least seven years of imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://law.moj.gov.tw/Eng/LawClass/LawContent.aspx?PCODE=C0000008|title=Laws & Regulations Database of The Republic of China|website=law.moj.gov.tw|access-date=2018-03-26}}</ref>

